<?xml version="1.0"?>
<config xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:magento:module:Magento_Config:etc/system_file.xsd">
    <system>
        <tab id="ethelserth" translate="label" sortOrder="400">
            <label>Ethelserth</label>
        </tab>
        <section id="ethelserth_checkout" translate="label" type="text" sortOrder="100" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
            <label>Checkout</label>
            <tab>ethelserth</tab>
            <resource>Ethelserth_Checkout::config</resource>
            <group id="address_lookup" translate="label" type="text" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>Address Lookup</label>
                <field id="enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Enable Postcode Lookup</label>
                    <comment>Shows a quick address lookup widget for NL/BE/DE customers. Requires a Postcoder API key.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="postcoder_api_key" translate="label comment" type="obscure" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Postcoder API Key</label>
                    <comment>Get your key at postcoder.com. Required when lookup is enabled.</comment>
                    <backend_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Backend\Encrypted</backend_model>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="newsletter" translate="label" type="text" sortOrder="15" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>Newsletter Subscription</label>
                <field id="enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Show Newsletter Checkbox at Checkout</label>
                    <comment>An opt-in checkbox above the place-order button that subscribes the shopper after a successful order. Also requires Magento's native "Allow Guest Subscription" flag (Stores &gt; Config &gt; Customers &gt; Newsletter) and an enabled Magento_Newsletter module.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="label" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Checkbox Label</label>
                    <comment>Translatable. Defaults to "Subscribe to our newsletter".</comment>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="notice" translate="label comment" type="textarea" sortOrder="30" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>GDPR / Consent Notice</label>
                    <comment>Small print rendered under the checkbox. Translatable. Override per-store with your privacy-policy link if your jurisdiction requires it.</comment>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="order_comments" translate="label" type="text" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>Order Comments</label>
                <field id="enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Enable Order Comments Field</label>
                    <comment>Shows a free-text "order notes" textarea during checkout. The text is sanitised (HTML stripped, control bytes removed, capped at 1000 chars) and stored on the quote and the placed order. Visible in the admin order view regardless of this toggle so historical comments stay readable if you turn it off later.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="placement" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Field Placement</label>
                    <comment>Where the textarea appears in the checkout. "Address step" sits above the Continue button (better for shoppers planning ahead, e.g. delivery instructions). "Payment step" sits above Place Order (better for last-minute notes, gift messages). Toggle this if your shoppers tell you the field feels misplaced.</comment>
                    <source_model>Ethelserth\Checkout\Model\Config\Source\OrderCommentsPlacement</source_model>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="label" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="30" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Field Label</label>
                    <comment>Translatable label shown above the textarea. Defaults to "Order notes (optional)".</comment>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="placeholder" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="40" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Placeholder</label>
                    <comment>Hint shown inside an empty textarea, e.g. "Delivery instructions, gift message, scheduling…".</comment>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
            </group>
        </section>
    </system>
</config>
